#from qiime2 object  to phyloseq object
df<-readr::read_tsv("rel-phyla-table.tsv")
## Rows: 81 Columns: 53
##  Column specification 
## Delimiter: "\t"
## chr  (1): #OTU ID
## dbl (52): 2010-RvD-d1-001, 2010-RvD-d1-004, 2010-RvD-d1-007, 2010-RvD-d1-010...
## 
##  Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
##  Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
df$`#OTU ID` <- gsub("^.*;g__","", df$`#OTU ID`)

#df = df[rowSums(is.na(df)) == 0,]
#df = df[rowSums(df[, -1] > 0) != 0, ]
mat = data.matrix(df)
rownames(mat) <- df$`#OTU ID`
mat = mat[,colnames(mat)!="#OTU ID"]
mat = mat[,colnames(mat)!="Wasserkontrolle1"]
mat = mat[,colnames(mat)!="Wasserkontrolle2"]
mat = mat[,colnames(mat)!="Wasserkontrolle3"]

CST<- readr::read_tsv("liu_cst.tsv")
## Rows: 49 Columns: 2
##  Column specification 
## Delimiter: "\t"
## chr (2): sample-id, CST
## 
##  Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
##  Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
CST2<-readr::read_tsv("liu_cst.tsv")
## Rows: 49 Columns: 2
##  Column specification 
## Delimiter: "\t"
## chr (2): sample-id, CST
## 
##  Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
##  Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
CST2$`sample-id` <- NULL
CST2 = as.data.frame(CST2)
rownames(CST2) <- CST$`sample-id`

# Euclidean distance by hierarchal clustering with Ward link-
  #age, as previously described  " liu et al., 2015


pheatmap(mat, main = "CSTs", treeheight_row = 5, treeheight_col = 5, show_colnames = 1, cluster_cols = T, annotation_col = CST2, ,cluster_rows = T, clustering_method = "ward.D", cex = .9)
